# EcoTox-AI: Aquatic Toxicity Prediction Platform

An AI-powered platform that predicts the ecotoxicity (LC50) of chemical compounds using molecular descriptors and machine learning, replacing weeks of wet-lab bioassays with instant predictions.

## Background

Traditional ecotoxicity testing requires culturing aquatic organisms (fish, daphnia) for 48–96 hours per compound. EcoTox-AI learns from thousands of known toxicity measurements to predict the **96-hour LC50** (Lethal Concentration killing 50% of test fish) for new molecules — reducing weeks of lab work to seconds.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Dataset**: We will use the **UCI QSAR Fish Toxicity Dataset** (908 chemicals, 6 molecular descriptors, LC50 for fathead minnow). You need to download this and place it in the project's `data/` folder. Download links are provided at the bottom of this plan.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Multi-Algorithm Training**: The plan trains **7 different algorithms** and builds an **ensemble/consensus model** from the top performers. This is the industry best practice — not a single-model approach.

> [!WARNING]
> **Python Environment**: This project requires Python 3.9+ with scientific libraries (scikit-learn, XGBoost, TensorFlow/Keras, pandas, etc.). We will create a `requirements.txt` and set up a virtual environment.

