### Phase 3 — Multi-Algorithm Training (The Core)

We will train **7 algorithms** plus a **consensus ensemble**, each with hyperparameter tuning via GridSearchCV/RandomizedSearchCV:

#### [NEW] [src/algorithms/regression/linear_regression_models.py](file:///d:/EcoToxAI/src/algorithms/regression/linear_regression_models.py)

| Model | Hyperparameters Tuned | Why Include It |
|---|---|---|
| **Ridge Regression** | alpha (regularization strength) | Baseline — simple, fast, interpretable |
| **Lasso Regression** | alpha | Feature selection via L1 regularization |
| **ElasticNet** | alpha, l1_ratio | Combines L1 + L2 for balanced regularization |

#### [NEW] [src/algorithms/regression/tree_based_regression_models.py](file:///d:/EcoToxAI/src/algorithms/regression/tree_based_regression_models.py)

| Model | Hyperparameters Tuned | Why Include It |
|---|---|---|
| **Random Forest** | n_estimators, max_depth, min_samples_split, min_samples_leaf, max_features | Robust, handles non-linearity, resistant to overfitting |
| **Gradient Boosting** | n_estimators, max_depth, learning_rate, subsample | Strong sequential learner |
| **XGBoost** | n_estimators, max_depth, learning_rate, subsample, colsample_bytree, reg_alpha, reg_lambda | State-of-the-art for tabular data, best accuracy-speed tradeoff |

#### [NEW] [src/algorithms/regression/support_vector_regression.py](file:///d:/EcoToxAI/src/algorithms/regression/support_vector_regression.py)

| Model | Hyperparameters Tuned | Why Include It |
|---|---|---|
| **SVR (RBF kernel)** | C, gamma, epsilon | Excellent for small datasets, captures complex boundaries |

#### [NEW] [src/algorithms/regression/knn_regression.py](file:///d:/EcoToxAI/src/algorithms/regression/knn_regression.py)

| Model | Hyperparameters Tuned | Why Include It |
|---|---|---|
| **KNN Regressor** | n_neighbors, weights, metric | Instance-based learning, good for local patterns |

#### [NEW] [src/algorithms/regression/neural_network_regression.py](file:///d:/EcoToxAI/src/algorithms/regression/neural_network_regression.py)

| Model | Architecture | Why Include It |
|---|---|---|
| **Deep MLP** | Input(6) → Dense(128,ReLU) → Dropout(0.3) → Dense(64,ReLU) → Dropout(0.2) → Dense(32,ReLU) → Dense(1) | Learns complex non-linear patterns, state-of-the-art potential |

- **Optimizer**: Adam with learning rate scheduling
- **Early stopping**: Patience=20, restore best weights
- **Batch normalization** between layers
- **Training**: 500 epochs max with early stopping

#### [NEW] [src/algorithms/regression/ensemble_regression.py](file:///d:/EcoToxAI/src/algorithms/regression/ensemble_regression.py)

| Model | Method | Why Include It |
|---|---|---|
| **Stacking Ensemble** | Top 3 models as base learners → Ridge as meta-learner | Consensus of best models always outperforms individuals |
| **Voting Ensemble** | Average predictions of top 3 models | Simpler consensus, often equally effective |

